CGosh darn Navy Dude, <br>
Always had to bail them out. thre of us machine gunners got into a fight with a bunch of swabbies in early 67 in Long Beach, the CO was going to ring our neck, but found out we were on our way to Nam and wasn't sure what to do with us. So when he asked us why, &quot;Why did you get into a fight with a bunch of swabbies,&quot; he asked.<br>
I proudly answered;<br>
&quot;TRADITION SIR,&quot; <br>
He was alughting so hard, he just motioned for us to get out of his office, and that was the last we heard of it. <br><br>
if you'll drop me an e-mail msg I'll show you how to get to thread #145, Heck I'll even draw you Navy folks a picture on how to get there. <br>
